Posted: Thu Nov 22, 2007 5:19 am
Well, I'll filing suit against my bank in the Small Claims Court this weekend I've been looking forward to this, though I was hoping more that they'd cave early. The SCC rocks - true, lawyer-free justice for the people, the way it should be - and normally resolves issues quite speedily. Unfortunately the OFT have setup a test case on the issue (unlawful bank charges) and both they and the FOS have agreed that they will not act any more to help consumers till after the test case. Banks, including mine, that agreed to cooperate with the OFT following the result of this test case have been exonerated from not taking action at this time. Still, that's the OFT and FOS - I still have recourse to the SCC and even if the bank persuade the judge to defer judgement till after the test case resolves next spring I will still have my claim filed. Apparently it's a good idea to file anyway even if the case gets delayed. I stand to recuperate over £2000. That will be used to pay off my outstanding debts and put a few hundred into a savings account.Fingers crossed [Edit] - OFT = Office of Fair Trading, consumer champions. FOS = Financial Ombudsman Service, a government industry regulator who can intervene in disputes between financial companies and consumers.
