So I decided it's time to prepare for a job search, because the duties of my current position are 75% payroll, and 75% of that is dealing with the university's payroll setup (which makes me seriously homicidal). Anyway, I was going to take my time in studying the current job market, matching my skills against those being requested, taking a couple months to polish up the critical ones, networking with the local HR chapter, etc. I attended a job seekers group run by the chapter and received some fantastic advice from a career management consultant. Great, come February or March I'll be an irresistible candidate.And then a casual online search turns up a job posting.... it's as if I wrote up a description of exactly the next step I want to take in my career. Whoa. They've been actively recruiting for the position since October, but perhaps it's been difficult to find someone with HR skills and IT skills with biotech/healthcare industry experience. That's me in a nutshell.Resume submitted this morning. Nervous whimpering starts now. Well, not right now, because I have to go deal with freakin' payroll stuff for the next two hours. But after that, whimpering!
